  "prompt": "How do you tie a tie?",
  "response": "Here's a basic method to tie a standard necktie knot (Four-in-Hand knot):\n\n1. Drape the tie around your neck with the wide end on your right side, hanging about a foot lower than the narrow end.\n\n2. Cross the wide part over the narrow end from right to left.\n\n3. Bring the wide end up and pass it up through the loop around your neck.\n\n4. Hold the front of the knot loosely with your index finger and bring the wide end down through the front loop.\n\n5. Hold the narrow end and slide the knot up to your collar, adjusting it for tightness and symmetry.\n\nThere are several other tie knots like the Windsor knot, Half-Windsor, and Pratt knot, each with slightly different techniques. Would you like me to explain one of those in more detail?",
